text\":\"**Finalizing object presentation**\\n\\nI don't need to make any modifications to the repository. It looks like we've already executed everything without changes, except maybe for the temporary files in /tmp. I’ll make sure that the final output is only the object itself. It's also important to confirm that there’s no markdown formatting involved. This way, it keeps things straightforward and clear for the user. I’m focused on keeping it clean and simple!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"jackrabbit-webdav is an in-process WebDAV server/client utility library, but its servlet-facing APIs are meaningful coverage targets and the resolved artifact declares javax.servlet:servlet-api as a provided dependency, so generated tests need that API added explicitly.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"javax.servlet:servlet-api:2.4\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The library exposes and implements servlet-based classes such as AbstractWebdavServlet, WebdavRequestImpl, DavServletRequest/DavServletResponse, InputContextImpl, and OutputContextImpl, while the artifact POM marks servlet-api as provided; tests that exercise these APIs need the old javax.servlet API on the test compile/runtime classpath.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker service or external Jackrabbit/WebDAV server is needed. Prefer in-process unit tests over network integration tests: instantiate request/response/context/method classes directly and use small HttpServletRequest/HttpServletResponse stubs where servlet-facing behavior is exercised. Use the legacy javax.servlet API, not jakarta.servlet. No special environment variables or system properties were found to be required.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"If servlet-api is omitted, tests covering servlet/server/request/response classes may fail to compile or load even though the library dependency resolves.\",\n    \"Avoid adding a full Jackrabbit webapp/JCR repository or live WebDAV server setup; the library documentation describes this artifact as interfaces and common utility classes, not a deployable server.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0310c1a2190ee98f016a42897682688196b014c2c9a8a0ff63\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2226, "output": 1164, "cacheRead": 33792, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37182, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782745441630, "responseId": "resp_0310c1a2190ee98f016a428962165c81968c6658a106f2e8c2"}, "toolResults": []}
